    text: "For the purposes of this law, the terms used have the following meanings: 1) public order and peace - is a harmonized state of mutual relations among citizens arising from their behavior in public places and the actions of authorities and organizations in public life aimed at ensuring equal conditions for the realization of human and minority rights and freedoms guaranteed by the Constitution; 2) public place - is a space accessible to an indefinite number of persons whose identity is not predetermined, under the same conditions or without special conditions; 3) offenses against public order and peace - are unlawful acts that endanger or disturb public order and peace in public places, create unrest or endanger the safety of citizens, obstruct the movement of citizens in public places or the realization of their rights and freedoms, offend morality, endanger the general safety of property, insult or obstruct officials or otherwise disturb public order and peace; 4) quarrel - is a verbal conflict between two or more persons; 5) shouting - is a verbal expression of strong intensity; 6) noise - is an unwanted or harmful sound of strong intensity; 7) permissible noise level - is the maximum noise level whose intensity is determined by regulations on environmental noise protection; 8) insult (offending) - is the act of belittling the personality of another person; 9) committing violence - is the application of physical or other force on the body of another person, capable of causing suffering or pain; 10) threat - is endangering the safety of another person by suggesting that some harm will be done, or attacking the life or body of that person or a person close to them; 11) brawl - is mutual violence between two or more persons consisting of striking with hands, other body parts, or objects; 12) indecent, rude, or reckless behavior - is the behavior of a person or taking actions in a public place that endanger the safety of citizens or disturb public order and peace, offend the morality of citizens, destroy or damage property; 13) unauthorized collection of voluntary contributions - is any collection of voluntary contributions contrary to the provisions of this law; 14) gambling - is playing for money or some other value, the outcome of which depends on chance; 15) prostitution - is providing sexual services for compensation in money or another value; 16) shooting with firearms and other weapons - is any shooting with firearms and other weapons in public places, which creates noise, using ammunition without projectiles. It will be considered that an offense or criminal act from this law has been committed in a public place even when the act is committed in a place that is not considered a public place under paragraph 1, item 2 of this article, if that place is accessible to sight or sound from a public place or the consequence occurred in a public place.",
