    text_local: "Ako se na adresi gde se dostavljanje ima izvršiti niko ne zatekne, ostaviće se u poštanskom sandučetu ili pribiti na vrata obaveštenje da lice kome je pismeno upućeno treba da ga preuzme u sudu u roku od 15 dana od dana pokušanog dostavljanja.\nPo proteku roka iz stava 1. ovog člana, pismeno će se istaći na oglasnoj tabli i internet stranici suda, ako za to postoje tehnički uslovi. Dostavljanje se smatra izvršenim po isteku roka od osam dana od dana isticanja pismena na oglasnoj tabli i internet stranici suda.\nObaveštenje iz stava 1. ovog člana sadrži: ime i prezime lica kome je pokušano dostavljanje, svojstvo u postupku, datum i čas kada je pokušano dostavljanje, adresu na kojoj je pokušano dostavljanje, naznaku da pismeno treba da preuzme u sudu i u kom roku uz upozorenje da će u slučaju ne preuzimanja kopija pismena biti istaknuta na oglasnoj tabli i na internet stranici suda, kao i da će se u tom slučaju po proteku roka od osam dana smatrati da je dostavljanje izvršeno.\nAko se utvrdi da je lice kome se pismeno ima dostaviti odsutno ili da privremeno boravi na drugoj adresi i da mu se zbog toga ne može pismeno na vreme predati, pismeno će se vratiti sudu uz naznačenje gde se odsutni nalazi, i kada i gde će mu se moći izvršiti dostavljanje pismena.\nAko se pri ponovljenom pokušaju pismeno ne može dostaviti u vreme i u mestu određenom na način iz stava 4. ovog člana, pismeno će se istaći na oglasnoj tabli i internet stranici suda ako za to postoje tehnički uslovi. Dostavljanje se smatra izvršenim po isteku roka od osam dana od dana isticanja pismena na oglasnoj tabli i internet stranici suda.\nAko pismeno ne može da se dostavi na adresu iz člana 158. stav 1. ovog zakona, sud će proveriti adresu i ako se pri ponovljenom pokušaju pismeno ne može dostaviti na adresu na kojoj je lice prijavljeno, postupiće se na način propisan u stavu 2. ovog člana.",
    text: "If no one is found at the address where delivery is to be made, a notice will be left in the mailbox or affixed to the door stating that the person to whom the document is addressed must collect it at the court within 15 days from the attempted delivery.\nAfter the expiration of the period referred to in paragraph 1 of this article, the document will be posted on the court's bulletin board and website, if technical conditions allow. Delivery is considered completed after the expiration of the period of eight days from the date of posting the document on the court's bulletin board and website.\nThe notice referred to in paragraph 1 of this article contains: the name and surname of the person to whom delivery was attempted, their status in the proceedings, the date and time when delivery was attempted, the address where delivery was attempted, an indication that the document must be collected at the court and within what timeframe, along with a warning that if it is not collected, a copy of the document will be posted on the court's bulletin board and website, and that in that case, after the expiration of the period of eight days, delivery will be considered completed.\nIf it is determined that the person to whom the document is to be delivered is absent or temporarily residing at another address, and therefore the document cannot be delivered on time, the document will be returned to the court with an indication of where the absent person is located and when and where the document can be delivered.\nIf upon a repeated attempt the document cannot be delivered at the time and place specified in the manner described in paragraph 4 of this article, the document will be posted on the court's bulletin board and website if technical conditions allow. Delivery is considered completed after the expiration of the period of eight days from the date of posting the document on the court's bulletin board and website.\nIf the document cannot be delivered to the address specified in Article 158, paragraph 1 of this law, the court will verify the address, and if upon a repeated attempt the document cannot be delivered to the address where the person is registered, the procedure will be conducted as prescribed in paragraph 2 of this article.",
    source_url: "https://www.paragraf.ba/propisi/republika-srpska/zakon-o-prekrsajima.html",
